[[cdo:11 nguŏk 30 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:11 goe̍h 30 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:十一月三十]] {{Lunisolar November}} '''November 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} and its day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft}} .
As with all other day‑30 occurrences in the Sino‑Japanese calendar, its appearance depends on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events == * {{ill|Enchō|ja|延長|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1204|ja|1204|12=draft}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Fujiwara Toshinari|ja|藤原俊成|12=draft}} , a waka poet, was dispatched (* {{ill|1114|ja|1114|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1546|ja|1546|12=draft}} {{ill|January 2|ja|1月2日|12=draft}} ) – The empress’s consort, {{ill|Myōkyū|ja|妙玖|12=draft}} , wife of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|12=draft}} , died (* {{ill|1499|ja|1499|12=draft}} ).
== Births == * {{ill|Suiko Tennō|ja|Empress Suiko|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} {{ill|592|ja|592|12=draft}} {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|12=draft}} ) – (Note: This birth record appears as a placeholder.)
== Deaths == * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文明|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1481|ja|1481|12=draft}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ikkyū Sōjun|ja|一休宗純|12=draft}} , a Rinzai monk and founder of the Nichiren sect (* {{ill|1394|ja|1394|12=draft}} )<ref>Reference: Encyclopedia Britannica</ref> * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1731|ja|1731|12=draft}} {{ill|January 5|ja|1月5日|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsuguyoshi|ja|徳川継友|12=draft}} , lord of the Owari Domain (* {{ill|1692|ja|1692|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Genbun|ja|元文|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1737|ja|1737|12=draft}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Mitsui Takahira|ja|三井高平|12=draft}} , founder of the precursor to the Mitsukoshi department store (child of {{ill|Mitsui Takatomi|ja|三井高利|12=draft}} ) (* {{ill|1653|ja|1653|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1829|ja|1829|12=draft}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft}} ) – The fourth-generation head of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|12=draft}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|ja|1755|12=draft}} ).
