As with all other day‑30 occurrences in the Sino‑Japanese calendar, its appearance depends on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> == Events == * {{ill|Enchō|ja|延長}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1204|ja|1204}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日}} ) – {{ill|Fujiwara Toshinari|ja|藤原俊成}} , a waka poet, was dispatched (* {{ill|1114|ja|1114}} ). * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1546|ja|1546}} {{ill|January 2|ja|1月2日}} ) – The empress’s consort, {{ill|Myōkyū|ja|妙玖}} , wife of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari}} , died (* {{ill|1499|ja|1499}} ). == Births == * {{ill|Suiko Tennō|ja|Empress Suiko}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|592|ja|592}} {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日}} ) – (Note: This birth record appears as a placeholder.) == Deaths == * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文明}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1481|ja|1481}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日}} ) – {{ill|Ikkyū Sōjun|ja|一休宗純}} , a Rinzai monk and founder of the Nichiren sect (* {{ill|1394|ja|1394}} )<ref>Reference: Encyclopedia Britannica</ref> * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1731|ja|1731}} {{ill|January 5|ja|1月5日}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsuguyoshi|ja|徳川継友}} , lord of the Owari Domain (* {{ill|1692|ja|1692}} ). * {{ill|Genbun|ja|元文|1=Genbun}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1737|ja|1737}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日}} ) – {{ill|Mitsui Takahira|ja|三井高平}} , founder of the precursor to the Mitsukoshi department store (child of {{ill|Mitsui Takatomi|ja|三井高利}} ) (* {{ill|1653|ja|1653}} ). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1829|ja|1829}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日}} ) – The fourth-generation head of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|ja|1755}} ).
