{{Lunisolar November|qq=}} 
'''November 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|12=draft}}  – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}}  and its day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|12=draft}} .

As with all other day‑30 occurrences in the Sino‑Japanese calendar, its appearance depends on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>

As with all other day 30s of the Sino‑Japanese calendar, this occurrence sometimes happens and sometimes does not, depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref>  Months are annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big|qq=}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small|qq=}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>

== Events ==
* {{ill|Enchō|ja|延長|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1204|ja|1204|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Fujiwara Toshinari|ja|藤原俊成|qq=|12=draft}} , a waka poet, was dispatched (* {{ill|1114|ja|1114|qq=|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1546|ja|1546|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|January 2|ja|1月2日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – The empress’s consort, {{ill|Myōkyū|ja|妙玖|qq=|12=draft}} , wife of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|qq=|12=draft}} , died (* {{ill|1499|ja|1499|qq=|12=draft}} ).
== Births ==
* {{ill|Suiko Tennō|ja|Empress Suiko|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|592|ja|592|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – (Note: This birth record appears as a placeholder.)
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Bunji|ja|文明|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1481|ja|1481|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ikkyū Sōjun|ja|一休宗純|qq=|12=draft}} , a Rinzai monk and founder of the Nichiren sect (* {{ill|1394|ja|1394|qq=|12=draft}} )<ref>Reference: Encyclopedia Britannica</ref>
* {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1731|ja|1731|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|January 5|ja|1月5日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsuguyoshi|ja|徳川継友|qq=|12=draft}} , lord of the Owari Domain (* {{ill|1692|ja|1692|qq=|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Genbun|ja|元文|1=Genbun|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1737|ja|1737|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Mitsui Takahira|ja|三井高平|qq=|12=draft}} , founder of the precursor to the Mitsukoshi department store (child of {{ill|Mitsui Takatomi|ja|三井高利|qq=|12=draft}} ) (* {{ill|1653|ja|1653|qq=|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|12=draft}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1829|ja|1829|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – The fourth-generation head of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|qq=|12=draft}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|ja|1755|qq=|12=draft}} ).

