[[cdo:11 nguŏk 30 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[de:November 30 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:November 30 (Lunisolar)]] [[ko:음력 11월 30일]] [[ja:11月30日 (旧暦)]] [[zh:十一月三十]] [[en:draft:November 30 (Lunisolar)]] [[en:11月30日 (旧暦)]] [[ar:November 30 (Lunisolar)]]

{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月三十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 30일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft}} and its day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft}} .
As with all other day‑30 occurrences in the Sino‑Japanese calendar, its appearance depends on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
As with all other day 30s of the Sino‑Japanese calendar, this occurrence sometimes happens and sometimes does not, depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref> Months are annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big|qq=}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small|qq=}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events == * {{ill|Enchō|ja|延長|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1204|ja|1204|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Fujiwara Toshinari|ja|藤原俊成|qq=|qq=draft}} , a waka poet, was dispatched (* {{ill|1114|ja|1114|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1546|ja|1546|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|January 2|ja|1月2日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – The empress’s consort, {{ill|Myōkyū|ja|妙玖|qq=|qq=draft}} , wife of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|qq=|qq=draft}} , died (* {{ill|1499|ja|1499|qq=|qq=draft}} ). == Births == * {{ill|Suiko Tennō|ja|Empress Suiko|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|592|ja|592|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – (Note: This birth record appears as a placeholder.) == Deaths == * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文明|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1481|ja|1481|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ikkyū Sōjun|ja|一休宗純|qq=|qq=draft}} , a Rinzai monk and founder of the Nichiren sect (* {{ill|1394|ja|1394|qq=|qq=draft}} )<ref>Reference: Encyclopedia Britannica</ref> * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=|qq=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1731|ja|1731|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|January 5|ja|1月5日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsuguyoshi|ja|徳川継友|qq=|qq=draft}} , lord of the Owari Domain (* {{ill|1692|ja|1692|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Genbun|ja|元文|1=Genbun|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1737|ja|1737|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Mitsui Takahira|ja|三井高平|qq=|qq=draft}} , founder of the precursor to the Mitsukoshi department store (child of {{ill|Mitsui Takatomi|ja|三井高利|qq=|qq=draft}} ) (* {{ill|1653|ja|1653|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|qq=draft}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1829|ja|1829|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – The fourth-generation head of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|qq=|qq=draft}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|ja|1755|qq=|qq=draft}} ).
