{{Not to be confused with|November 30|qq=November 30}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月三十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 30일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}} .
As with all other day‑30 occurrences in the Sino‑Japanese calendar, its appearance depends on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
As with all other day 30s of the Sino‑Japanese calendar, this occurrence sometimes happens and sometimes does not, depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref> Months are annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big|qq=}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small|qq=}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events == * {{ill|Enchō|ja|延長|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enchō|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Shunzei|Fujiwara Toshinari]] , a waka poet, was dispatched (* [[:en:1114|1114]] ). * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon (era)|qq=}} 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1546|1546]] [[:en:January 2|January 2]] ) – The empress’s consort, [[:en:Lady Myōkyū|Myōkyū]] , wife of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mōri Motonari|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , died (* [[:en:1499|1499]] ). == Births == * {{ill|Suiko Tennō|ja|Empress Suiko|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suiko Tennō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:592|592]] [[:en:December 12|December 12]] ) – (Note: This birth record appears as a placeholder.) == Deaths == * [[:en:Civilization|Bunji]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1481|1481]] [[:en:December 18|December 18]] ) – [[:en:Ikkyū|Ikkyū Sōjun]] , a Rinzai monk and founder of the Nichiren sect (* [[:en:1394|1394]] )<ref>Reference: Encyclopedia Britannica</ref> * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1731|1731]] [[:en:January 5|January 5]] ) – [[:en:Tokugawa Tsugutomo|Tokugawa Tsuguyoshi]] , lord of the Owari Domain (* [[:en:1692|1692]] ). * [[:en:Genbun|Genbun]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1737|1737]] [[:en:December 18|December 18]] ) – {{ill|Mitsui Takahira|ja|三井高平|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsui Takahira|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 三井八郎右衛門}} , founder of the precursor to the Mitsukoshi department store (child of [[:en:Mitsui Takatoshi|Mitsui Takatomi]] ) (* [[:en:1653|1653]] ). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 12th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1829|1829]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – The fourth-generation head of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuruyanin|qq=}} , a kabuki dramatist (* [[:en:1755|1755]] ).
